Both required files have been written.

**Summary of what was done.** Ran 10 iterations of propose-test-update on the 50,000-patient ds001_aml cohort (objective_response prevalence 16.9%). Tests included univariable chi-square / logistic regression for treatments, mutations, cytogenetics, demographics, labs, and SNPs; treatment-by-biomarker interaction logits (FLT3 inhibitors × FLT3, IDH inhibitors × IDH, fitness × VEN/AZA, complex karyotype × 7+3, TP53 × treatments); and a multivariable logistic model.

**Headline findings.** Strong supported effects: ecog_ps (negative, p<1e-97), idh1_mutation main effect (+5.6% ORR, p≈1e-17), albumin (+) / blast% (−) / WBC (−) / CRP (−) / weight_loss (−), VEN/AZA × unfit_for_intensive interaction (+, p=0.036), complex_karyotype × 7+3 interaction (−, p=0.0016). Notably refuted / paradoxical: FLT3 inhibitors do not benefit FLT3-mutated patients; ivosidenib is associated with significantly *lower* response in IDH1+ patients (interaction p=0.027) — opposite the mechanistic expectation; classical adverse markers (TP53, complex karyotype as a main effect, secondary AML) show no prognostic signal; no SNP survives Bonferroni; the unadjusted race/ORR gradient is fully explained by ECOG/age confounding.

**Outputs.** `transcript.json` (10 iterations, schema-conformant, with hypothesis IDs, signed effect estimates, and p-values) and `analysis_summary.txt` (narrative synthesis) in the working directory.
